<sect>Introduction

<p>
The kmail Team welcomes you to <tt> KMail</tt>. The comfortable mailer for the K Desktop Environment. We set our goal towards making a beautiful & intuitive mailer on the one hand side but on the other making it as powerfull as possible. Please enjoy using kmail. Bug reports & suggestions should go to one of the developers or to the kmail mailing list.
<p>
We hope you will enjoy this Mailer,
<p>
<tt>Markus Wubben</tt>
<p>
<htmlurl url="mailto:markus.wuebben@kde.org" name="markus.wuebben@kde.org">
<p>

<sect>How to get started...
<p>
This will be a very short introduction to kmail and its usage so you can start
working with it right away! For more in depth information see the Features section.

<sect1> KMail's first invokation....
<p>
Invoking kmail for the first time it will create a Directory and some files
in your home directory. 
This is the "~/Mail" directory which holds the initial folders (outbox,sent-mail,trash 
& inbox).
<p>
<sect2> Ok,looks good...what now?
<p>
The main screen is devided into 3 parts:<p>
1. The folder widget (upper left widget).<p>
2. The mail header widget (upper right widget).<p>
3. The reader widget (lower widget).<p>
Clicking a folder will open it and display the messages in the header widget.
Most likely there won't be any messages visible on kmail's first start.
Clicking one of the headers will make the message appear in the reader widget.

<sect2> Setting up kmail
<p>
Please select "Settings" from the "File" - menu. In this Tabdialog you now have to 
enter some initial information so kmail can work correctly. In addition you can  
specify some preferences to adjust kmail to your needs.

<p>
<sect> Features and Details
<sect1>Folders and Accounts
<p>
KMail allows you to have multiple folders and accounts. The philosophy is that you have certain accounts connected to certain folders. You can easily create, modify & delete folders and accounts via the menubar items.
<p>

<sect1>Drag and Drop
<p>
KMail makes use of the KDE Drag and Drop protocol. This means that you can darg
and drop message form the header widget to your desktop or drop attachments on the composer to be automatically attached.
<p>

<sect1>Pretty good privacy
<p>
Sorry but this feature is not yet implemented.
<p>

